abstract: Venezuela's pro-government Constituent Assembly on Monday approved a trial for four opposition lawmakers accused of committing crimes including treason and conspiracy.
snippet: Venezuela's pro-government Constituent Assembly on Monday approved a trial for four opposition lawmakers accused of committing crimes including treason and conspiracy.
lead_paragraph: CARACAS — Venezuela's pro-government Constituent Assembly on Monday approved a trial for four opposition lawmakers accused of committing crimes including treason and conspiracy.
headline_main: Venezuela's Constituent Assembly Approves Trial of Four Opposition Lawmakers
headline_print_headline: Venezuela's Constituent Assembly Approves Trial of Four Opposition Lawmakers

abstract: Matteo Salvini, the leader of Italy's right-wing League party, has suddenly dropped his calls for the government to resign and is instead proposing that all the main parties work together to solve the country's most pressing problems.
snippet: Matteo Salvini, the leader of Italy's right-wing League party, has suddenly dropped his calls for the government to resign and is instead proposing that all the main parties work together to solve the country's most pressing problems.
lead_paragraph: ROME — Matteo Salvini, the leader of Italy's right-wing League party, has suddenly dropped his calls for the government to resign and is instead proposing that all the main parties work together to solve the country's most pressing problems.
headline_main: Italy's Salvini Drops Calls for Government to Quit, Urges Unity on Reforms
headline_print_headline: Italy's Salvini Drops Calls for Government to Quit, Urges Unity on Reforms

abstract: New York’s law allowing undocumented immigrants to obtain licenses went into effect on Monday. The same day, New Jersey passed a similar bill.
snippet: New York’s law allowing undocumented immigrants to obtain licenses went into effect on Monday. The same day, New Jersey passed a similar bill.
lead_paragraph: On the New York side of the Hudson River, lines outside some Department of Motor Vehicles offices stretched for blocks on Monday, as people sought to take advantage of a new state law allowing undocumented immigrants to obtain driver’s licenses.

abstract: Democrats in the key swing state of Wisconsin vowed Monday to redouble efforts to ensure that any voters whose registrations have been nullified by a judge's recent ruling will be able to register again before the 2020 presidential election.
snippet: Democrats in the key swing state of Wisconsin vowed Monday to redouble efforts to ensure that any voters whose registrations have been nullified by a judge's recent ruling will be able to register again before the 2020 presidential election.
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — Democrats in the key swing state of Wisconsin vowed Monday to redouble efforts to ensure that any voters whose registrations have been nullified by a judge's recent ruling will be able to register again before the 2020 presidential election.
headline_main: Wisconsin Democrats Vow to Register Voters Who May Be Purged
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Democrats Vow to Register Voters Who May Be Purged

abstract: A temporary cut in federal taxes on alcohol fueled the growth of American distilleries, but its expiration threatens their demise.
snippet: A temporary cut in federal taxes on alcohol fueled the growth of American distilleries, but its expiration threatens their demise.
lead_paragraph: The last two years have been good ones for Lyon Distilling. At the small rum producer in St. Michaels, Md., a town on the Eastern Shore of Chesapeake Bay, production has jumped from 4,000 bottles a year to 40,000. Four employees have become 15.

abstract: Goldman Sachs Group Inc outlined plans on Monday to put money and advice toward projects that fight climate change or help financially disadvantaged people, with executives arguing it is not only the right thing to do but can generate income.
snippet: Goldman Sachs Group Inc outlined plans on Monday to put money and advice toward projects that fight climate change or help financially disadvantaged people, with executives arguing it is not only the right thing to do but can generate income.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Goldman Sachs Group Inc outlined plans on Monday to put money and advice toward projects that fight climate change or help financially disadvantaged people, with executives arguing it is not only the right thing to do but can generate income.
headline_main: Goldman Sachs Says It Will Support 'Green' Initiatives More Forcefully
headline_print_headline: Goldman Sachs Says It Will Support 'Green' Initiatives More Forcefully

abstract: Zahara Kamperveen laid white lilies before a glossy black plaque, then gently touched the name of her grandfather, a radio-station owner executed by a military junta in Suriname along with 14 other men nearly two decades before she was born.
snippet: Zahara Kamperveen laid white lilies before a glossy black plaque, then gently touched the name of her grandfather, a radio-station owner executed by a military junta in Suriname along with 14 other men nearly two decades before she was born.
lead_paragraph: PARAMARIBO, Suriname — Zahara Kamperveen laid white lilies before a glossy black plaque, then gently touched the name of her grandfather, a radio-station owner executed by a military junta in Suriname along with 14 other men nearly two decades before she was born.
headline_main: Convicted in Massacre, Suriname's Leader Hangs on Tight
headline_print_headline: Convicted in Massacre, Suriname's Leader Hangs on Tight

abstract: Construction of the U.S.N.S. Harvey Milk, a fleet oiler, began last week in San Diego.
